Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

Andropogon chinensis

Photo by Richard Gill. Source: iNaturalist, licensed under CC BY-NC

The assembly is haploid, and the genome is tetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 1300 Mb, and has 20 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Andropogon chinensis from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 2 from the main text, with Andropogon chinensis highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Andropogon chinensis vs.Paspalum vaginatum

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Andropogon chinensis along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Andropogon chinensis is a tetraploid with a haploid assembly, we expect 2 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Andropogon chinensis

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Andropogon chinensis along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum gene index on the x-axis. As Andropogon chinensis is a tetraploid with a haploid assembly, we expect 2 lines, one for each subgenome.
